President Obama has declared a major disaster in Virginia due to an earthquake that occurred between August 23 and October 25, 2011. This declaration allows for federal funding to assist individuals in Louisa County affected by the earthquake. Assistance may include grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for property losses, and other programs for recovery. Federal funding is also available for hazard mitigation measures on a cost-sharing basis for all counties and independent cities in Virginia. Donald L. Keldsen has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Residents and business owners in the designated counties can begin applying for assistance through an online registration or by calling specific phone numbers.